<glossary>
<definition id="def-00001"><term>microcytic anemia</term><meaning>anemia that is marked by abnormally small red blood cells. Example: Iron-deficient anemia</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00002"><term>macrocytic anemia</term><meaning>anemia that is marked by abnormally large red blood cells. Example: Folate and vitamin B<sub>12</sub> deficient anemia</meaning></definition>
<definition id="def-00003"><term>pica</term><meaning>craving and chewing substances with no nutritional value such as ice, dirt, clay, and paper</meaning></definition>
</glossary>
